comments: Basic spanish speaking skills, and knowledge of spanish speaking countries.
I got a good foundation for my Spanish language skills.
I learned how to read, write, and speak Spanish at a higher proficiency than I entered the course with.

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments: The professor was understanding and provided support when asked. She also replied to emails very quickly, ensuring prompt communication.

Strengths of the course was the pacing and the instructor. She was incredibly engaging and super helpful. I loved all of the in-class activities and the projects never felt superfluous or unnecessary. Weaknesses were iLearn and how many assignments we actually had to do on the platform which was ridden with bugs and errors.
